{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DHPqLdoUvisPx9B1amfkZa","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Foundations\n     2→\n     3→Cross-cutting patterns that affect every game and every package. These topics require firm decisions before Phase 1 implementation begins.\n     4→\n     5→**Status key**: `[DECIDED]` = locked, `[OPEN]` = needs discussion, `[DRAFT]` = proposal exists but not locked.\n     6→\n     7→---\n     8→\n     9→## 1) Testing Methodology `[DRAFT]`\n    10→\n    11→### Principles\n    12→- **Local-first**: All testing optimized for local dev experience. CI shape is deferred.\n    13→- **No blanket methodology**: Different features need different test approaches. Define strategy per feature/package, not one-size-fits-all.\n    14→- **Coverage guides, not gates**: Strive for coverage on critical paths but no hard thresholds that block work.\n    15→- **Zero mocks target**: Mocks are retired as real implementations land. No adapter layers or feature flags — delete the mock.\n    16→- **Test data is setup/teardown**: Each test seeds its own state (airdrop SOL, create accounts, deploy programs as needed). No shared fixtures.\n    17→\n    18→### Layers\n    19→\n    20→| Layer | Scope | Tooling | Runs Against |\n    21→|-------|-------|---------|--------------|\n    22→| Unit | State machines, payout math, fee calc, HMAC, VRF proof validation | vitest | In-process (no chain) |\n    23→| Component | React components — structural regression | @testing-library/react + vitest (DOM snapshots) | JSDOM |\n    24→| On-chain (program) | Anchor program correctness (instructions, accounts, constraints) | bankrun | In-process simulated validator |\n    25→| Integration | Frontend ↔ chain round-trips (connect, bet, resolve, payout) | Playwright + solana-test-validator | Local validator + headless Chromium |\n    26→| Visual regression | Key pages/flows — pixel-diff to catch UI breakage | Playwright screenshot comparison | Local dev server + headless Chromium |\n    27→\n    28→### Key Decisions\n    29→- **bankrun** for pure Anchor program tests: fast, in-process, no RPC server needed. Handles account creation, program deployment, slot advancement internally.\n    30→- **solana-test-validator** for anything the frontend touches: exposes localhost RPC so the browser can connect. Setup script deploys programs + seeds accounts before tests run.\n    31→- **Playwright** over Cypress: runs headless Chromium natively in devcontainers, lighter footprint.\n    32→- **DOM snapshots** (vitest) for lightweight structural regression on components.\n    33→- **Playwright screenshot comparison** for visual regression on full pages/flows — catches design and UX breakage when adding features.\n    34→- **No Storybook**: not adding a component catalog build artifact.\n    35→\n    36→### Per-Feature Test Strategy (Define As We Go)\n    37→Not every test type applies to every feature. When implementing a feature, define which layers apply. Example thinking:\n    38→- Coinflip state machine → unit tests (vitest)\n    39→- Coinflip lobby UI → DOM snapshot + visual regression\n    40→- Coinflip VRF resolution → on-chain program test (bankrun)\n    41→- Coinflip full flow → integration (Playwright + local validator)\n    42→- Crash multiplier curve → unit test (pure math)\n    43→- Crash real-time chart → visual regression may not be meaningful (animation); consider threshold-based assertions instead\n    44→\n    45→### Open Questions (Deferred)\n    46→- CI pipeline shape: deferred until local testing is solid.\n    47→- Coverage thresholds: revisit after Phase 1 features land.\n    48→- Playwright visual regression baseline: when do we capture initial screenshots?\n    49→\n    50→---\n    51→\n    52→## 2) On-Chain Dev Loop `[DRAFT]`\n    53→\n    54→### Iteration Flow\n    55→Default loop: `anchor test` (spins up local validator → deploys programs → runs tests → tears down).\n    56→No persistent local validator during regular dev. Devnet is not the iteration target.\n    57→\n    58→### Program Architecture\n    59→Separate deployable programs per game + a platform program for shared on-chain state.\n    60→\n    61→| Program | Type | Purpose |\n    62→|---------|------|---------|\n    63→| `solana/programs/coinflip` | Deployable | Coinflip game logic, settlement |\n    64→| `solana/programs/crash` | Deployable | Crash game logic, settlement |\n    65→| `solana/programs/platform` | Deployable | Platform settings, player profiles, per-game player metadata |\n    66→| `solana/shared` | Rust lib crate (not deployed) | Common types, fee constants, utility functions |\n    67→\n    68→- Games CPI into `platform` to read settings and update player profiles after settlement.\n    69→- Each game program has its own program ID and can be deployed/upgraded independently.\n    70→- `shared` is compiled into each program at build time, not deployed on-chain.\n    71→- **Legacy note**: Existing `solana/` code is leftover scaffolding — does not influence future design.\n    72→\n    73→### On-Chain State (Platform Program)\n    74→- **Platform settings account**: Fee rates, pause state, global config.\n    75→- **Player profile PDA** (per wallet): Aggregate stats, history metadata.\n    76→- **Per-game player accounts**: Game-specific stats/metadata, created on first play.\n    77→\n    78→### IDL Pipeline\n    79→1. `anchor build` → generates IDL JSON in `target/idl/` + TS types in `target/types/`\n    80→2. `scripts/sync-idl` → copies generated types into a TS package (e.g. `packages/anchor-client/`)\n    81→3. Frontend imports typed program interfaces from that package.\n    82→\n    83→Script is manual (`pnpm sync-idl`), not a post-build hook.\n    84→\n    85→### Mock Retirement\n    86→Mocks are deleted as real implementations land. No adapter layers, no feature flags. When a program is deployed and testable via `anchor test`, the corresponding mock goes away.\n    87→\n    88→### Open Questions (Deferred)\n    89→- Devnet deployment strategy: deferred until local loop is solid.\n    90→- Program upgrade authority management: single key vs multisig.\n    91→\n    92→---\n    93→\n    94→## 3) Wallet Strategy `[DECIDED: wallet-adapter]`\n    95→\n    96→**Decision**: Use `@solana/wallet-adapter-react` for V1. Privy deferred to V1.5.\n    97→**Ref**: `docs/DECISIONS.md` — \"Normal Wallets First, Privy Later\"\n    98→\n    99→### Impact\n   100→- `packages/wallet/` needs significant refactor (currently has Privy scaffolding)\n   101→- Supported wallets: Phantom, Solflare, Backpack (wallet-adapter defaults)\n   102→- Mock wallet provider gets retired once wallet-adapter is wired (zero mocks target)\n   103→\n   104→### Migration Notes\n   105→- Strip Privy imports and session-key logic from packages/wallet\n   106→- Replace with wallet-adapter provider + hook wiring\n   107→- Connection flow: standard `useWallet()` → `connect()` → sign transaction\n   108→\n   109→---\n   110→\n   111→## 4) Error Taxonomy `[DRAFT]`\n   112→\n   113→### Architecture\n   114→- **Programs** define `#[error_code]` enums with numeric codes + short dev messages (for logs/debugging).\n   115→- **Shared TS package** (`packages/errors/` or within `packages/anchor-client/`) maps error codes → user-facing strings + severity + category.\n   116→- **Frontend** reads severity and picks the presentation pattern. No retry logic — user always retries manually.\n   117→\n   118→### Error Code Ranges (Per Program)\n   119→Each deployable program owns a code range to avoid collisions:\n   120→- `platform`: 6000–6099\n   121→- `coinflip`: 6100–6199\n   122→- `crash`: 6200–6299\n   123→- (Reserve ranges for future games)\n   124→\n   125→### Error Categories\n   126→| Source | Examples | Handling |\n   127→|--------|----------|----------|\n   128→| Program error | Insufficient funds, invalid bet, game already resolved | Map code → user message via shared package |\n   129→| Transaction failure | RPC timeout, slot expired, blockhash expired | Surface to user, manual retry |\n   130→| Wallet rejection | User cancelled in wallet popup | Informational, no retry prompt |\n   131→| Network error | WebSocket disconnect, RPC unreachable | Surface to user, manual retry |\n   132→\n   133→### UX Presentation (Severity-Based)\n   134→- **Toast**: Transient/retryable errors (network timeout, RPC hiccup, slot expired)\n   135→- **Inline**: Validation errors near the action (bet too low, insufficient balance)\n   136→- **Modal**: Blocking/fatal errors needing acknowledgment (game cancelled, unexpected on-chain state)\n   137→\n   138→### Principles\n   139→- English only for V1. No i18n.\n   140→- User-facing copy lives client-side, never in on-chain programs.\n   141→- No automatic retry — always surface the error and let the user decide.\n   142→- Same error code can have different UX in different contexts (e.g. \"insufficient funds\" is inline on bet form, toast on auto-cashout failure).\n   143→\n   144→### Open Questions (Deferred)\n   145→- Exact error enum definitions: defined when each program is implemented.\n   146→- Toast/notification component: depends on UI package decisions.\n   147→\n   148→---\n   149→\n   150→## 5) Randomness Strategy `[DRAFT]`"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_017Yu3A84GWfFXspsRfxzQMN","session_id":"1e81398f-978c-4fff-848f-a37f36dac162","uuid":"74f504ee-068b-49d4-ac21-9b9fae960736"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017Yu3A84GWfFXspsRfxzQMN","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a summary of all the findings.\n\n## Test Infrastructure Summary\n\nBased on thorough exploration of the test infrastructure in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/`, here's what I found:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Visual Regression Test Architecture\n\n**Framework**: Playwright (v1.58.2) with custom fixtures for visual regression testing.\n\n**Key Configuration** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/playwright.config.ts`):\n- **Test directory**: `./e2e`\n- **Workers**: 1 (sequential execution to avoid interference)\n- **Retries**: 0 (no automatic retries)\n- **Viewport**: 1280x1080 (Desktop Chrome)\n- **Base URL**: `http://localhost:3000`\n- **Snapshot tolerance**: `maxDiffPixelRatio: 0.015` (1.5% pixel difference allowed)\n- **Snapshot path**: `{testDir}/__snapshots__/{testFilePath}/{arg}{ext}` (organized by test file)\n\n---\n\n### 2. Dev Server Startup in Tests\n\n**Web Server Config** (in `playwright.config.ts`):\n```typescript\nwebServer: {\n  command: \"pnpm dev\",           // Runs Vite dev server\n  url: \"http://localhost:3000\",  // Waits for this URL to respond\n  reuseExistingServer: !process.env.CI,  // Local dev can reuse running server\n  timeout: 30_000,               // 30s timeout for server startup\n}\n```\n\n**How it works**:\n- Playwright automatically starts `pnpm dev` before tests run\n- Waits for port 3000 to be responsive before proceeding\n- Reuses existing server in local dev (faster iteration)\n- Always starts fresh in CI\n- The dev server runs Vite with standard config from `vite.config.ts` (port 3000, React plugin, path aliases)\n\n---\n\n### 3. Test Utilities and Fixtures\n\n**Main Fixture**: `stablePage` (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/fixtures.ts`)\n\nThe `stablePage` fixture extends Playwright's default `page` with comprehensive determinism features:\n\n**a) Deterministic Randomness**:\n- Seeds `Math.random()` with Mulberry32 PRNG (seed: 42)\n- Seeds `crypto.getRandomValues()` for consistent `Keypair.generate()` behavior\n- Freezes `Date.now()` to fixed timestamp (2026-01-01T00:00:00Z)\n\n**b) Animation Freezing**:\n```typescript\nconst FREEZE_CSS = `\n  *, *::before, *::after {\n    animation-duration: 0s !important;\n    animation-delay: 0s !important;\n    transition-duration: 0s !important;\n    transition-delay: 0s !important;\n    scroll-behavior: auto !important;\n  }\n  svg { animation-play-state: paused !important; }\n`;\n```\n- Injected on every navigation\n- Pauses SVG SMIL animations via JS\n- Ensures stable screenshots without animation frames\n\n**c) Loading and Stabilization**:\n- Overrides `page.goto()` to automatically:\n  - Wait for `networkidle` state\n  - Wait for `document.fonts.ready` (prevents font rendering differences)\n  - Add 300ms settle time for remaining paints\n  - Re-inject animation freeze CSS after navigation\n\n**d) Console Error Collection**:\n- Captures all console errors during test execution\n- Automatically fails test if any console errors detected\n- Provides detailed error output at test completion\n\n---\n\n### 4. VITE_MOCK_MODE Handling\n\n**Environment Variable**: `VITE_MOCK_MODE` (default: `true`)\n\n**Configuration Files**:\n- `.env.example`: Sets `VITE_MOCK_MODE=true` as default\n- `.env.devnet`: No VITE_MOCK_MODE set (uses real wallet for devnet testing)\n\n**Implementation** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/wallet/src/WalletProvider.tsx`):\n\n```typescript\nfunction isMockMode(): boolean {\n  const flag = import.meta.env?.VITE_MOCK_MODE;\n  // Default to mock mode when unset or explicitly \"true\"\n  return flag === undefined || flag === \"\" || flag === \"true\";\n}\n\nexport function WalletProvider({ children }: WalletProviderProps) {\n  const inner = isMockMode() ? (\n    <MockWalletProvider>{children}</MockWalletProvider>\n  ) : (\n    <Suspense fallback={null}>\n      <RealWalletProvider>{children}</RealWalletProvider>\n    </Suspense>\n  );\n  \n  return <ConnectionProvider endpoint={endpoint}>{inner}</ConnectionProvider>;\n}\n```\n\n**Behavior**:\n- Mock mode is the default (visual regression tests run against mock wallet)\n- Real wallet adapter is lazy-loaded (only bundled when needed)\n- Tests automatically use mock mode since no .env.local overrides VITE_MOCK_MODE\n\n**Mock Wallet Features** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/wallet/src/mock/`):\n- Generates deterministic keypairs (via seeded PRNG in tests)\n- Persists to localStorage (`\"rng-utopia-mock-wallet\"`) by default\n- Tests clear localStorage to ensure clean state: `localStorage.removeItem(\"rng-utopia-mock-wallet\")`\n- Initial balance: 1000 SOL (configurable)\n- Simulated latency: 500ms (configurable)\n- 5% random transaction failure rate\n- Exposes `updateBalance()`, `getBalance()`, and `getBalanceLamports()` for test control\n\n---\n\n### 5. Test Organization\n\n**Test Files**:\n1. **Route Baselines** (`e2e/visual/routes.spec.ts`):\n   - 12 full-page snapshots of all routes\n   - Tests: home, coinflip, lord-of-rngs, close-call, crash, game-of-trades, profile, quests, loot, fairness, leaderboard, 404\n\n2. **State Variants** (`e2e/visual/states.spec.ts`):\n   - Tests wallet connected/disconnected states\n   - Covers: home (connected/disconnected), profile (connected), coinflip (connected/disconnected)\n   - Each test explicitly clears localStorage and connects wallet manually for determinism\n\n**Snapshot Storage**:\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/__snapshots__/visual/`\n- Organized by test file: `routes.spec.ts/`, `states.spec.ts/`\n- 17 total snapshot images captured\n\n**Commands**:\n- Run tests: `pnpm test:visual` (or `playwright test`)\n- Update snapshots: `pnpm test:visual:update` (or `playwright test --update-snapshots`)\n\n---\n\n### Key Testing Principles (from `docs/FOUNDATIONS.md`)\n\n1. **Zero mocks target**: Mocks are retired as real implementations land. No adapter layers or feature flags — delete the mock.\n2. **Visual regression**: Playwright screenshot comparison catches design and UX breakage when adding features.\n3. **Local-first**: All testing optimized for local dev experience. CI shape deferred.\n4. **Test data is setup/teardown**: Each test seeds its own state (clear localStorage, connect wallet explicitly). No shared fixtures.\n5. **Coverage guides, not gates**: Strive for coverage on critical paths but no hard thresholds that block work.\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\nThe test infrastructure is well-architected for deterministic visual regression testing:\n- **Playwright** manages server startup and browser automation\n- **stablePage fixture** ensures pixel-perfect reproducibility through seeded randomness, frozen time, disabled animations, and font loading\n- **VITE_MOCK_MODE** defaults to true, making tests run against a deterministic mock wallet\n- **Test organization** covers route baselines and state variants with full-page snapshots\n- **Console error tracking** automatically fails tests on JS errors\n- All tests are isolated (clear localStorage, manual wallet connection) to prevent flakiness"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a15f5d0 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 46046\ntool_uses: 30\nduration_ms: 110842</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1e81398f-978c-4fff-848f-a37f36dac162","uuid":"2a8c7877-d0fd-42d0-a1eb-b14b0fd77d03","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the test infrastructure for this project. Find and summarize:\n1. How visual regression tests work — look at `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/tests/` for Playwright test files\n2. How the dev server is started in tests — look for playwright.config.ts or similar\n3. What